      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in stopping major 21st-century wars as a qualified failure, largely due to the paralysis of the Security Council. The organization is consistently undermined by the veto power wielded by permanent members, which allows great power politics to override collective security mandates. Therefore, while it manages humanitarian crises, its structural inability to enforce peace against determined aggressors renders it largely ineffective in preventing large-scale conflict.",
